# React & styles

## React (App.jsx)

- Functional components only; hooks: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useMemo`.
- No router; view switching via `viewMode` and conditional render (`viewMode === 'study' && <StudyView ... />`).
- Study card: single column layout — question always visible; answer and why-box only when `flipped === true`; keep meta grid (Seen, Correct, Ease) always visible below. Use `.answer-block` with small top margin (e.g. 12px), not a separate overlapping "back face".
- Props: pass callbacks and primitives (e.g. `onFlip`, `flipped`, `activeCard`). No prop drilling beyond one level for view-specific handlers.

## CSS (styles.css)

- Use `:root` variables for colors and shadow; avoid hardcoded hex in new rules.
- Class names: BEM-like (e.g. `flashcard-inner`, `answer-block`, `meta-grid`, `compact-study`). No inline styles except for dynamic values (e.g. bar width, SVG).
- Responsive: existing breakpoints at 1320px, 1180px, 760px for grids and shell; new layout changes should consider these.
- Panel/chrome: `.glass` for panels; `.panel-header`, `.button-row.spread`, `.top-gap` for spacing.
